<li>Ledger admins (the member who created the ledger) have additional controls, including inviting/removing members, and initiating ledger deletion.</li>
<li><strong>If a ledger admin deletes a ledger</strong>, it is locked for new entries immediately, and other members have <strong>3 days</strong> to save an archived copy for their own records before the original is permanently removed. This happens automatically; admin approval from other members is not required.</li>
